-- Hong Kong shares at new 3-1/2-year highs, property strong
-- By Grace Li
-- Tue Jul 29, 2014 04:06AM EDT
-- None



HONG KONG, July 29 (Reuters) - Hong Kong's benchmark index ended at its highest in more than 3-1/2 years on Tuesday, as gains accelerated in the afternoon with property developers strong ahead of interim earnings.

The Hang Seng Index <.HSI> closed up 0.9 percent at 24,640.53 points, its highest since November 2010. The China Enterprises Index <.HSCE> of the leading offshore Chinese listings in Hong Kong climbed 0.5 percent to finish at its highest since Dec. 10.  Both indexes had their sixth daily gain in a row on Tuesday.